title: Zoo Walkthrough 4 — Keeper's Farewell and the Staff Area
story: friendly-zoo
description: Chained full-playthrough, chapter 4 of 5. The witnessed-only keeper departure, the staff-gate Optional clause (absorbs the old wt-04 optional proof, ADR-196 C1), and the supply room. Continues from wt-03.
---

# The keeper waited, unwitnessed, past closing — his once-only farewell
# fires the moment we arrive (D11: `, once` cannot burn off-stage).
> west
[OK: contains "Main Path"]
[OK: contains "Zoo's all yours"]
[OK: contains "engine start and fade into the distance"]

# Gate CLOSED: the Optional clause is absent, the sentence ends cleanly.
> examine staff gate
[OK: contains "The staff gate is set into the fence."]
[OK: not contains "standing wide open"]

# The gate ships unlocked — the keycard errand is a red herring.
> unlock staff gate with keycard
[OK: contains "already unlocked"]

> open staff gate
[OK: contains "You open the staff gate"]

# Gate OPEN: the Optional clause renders inline, before the period.
> examine staff gate
[OK: contains "The staff gate is set into the fence, standing wide open."]

# Turn 27: the third feeding call rides the walk into the supply room.
> south
[OK: contains "Supply Room"]
[OK: contains "flashlight"]

> read warning sign
[OK: contains "CAUTION"]
[OK: contains "Great Owl Incident of 2022"]

> take flashlight
[OK: contains "Taken"]

> turn on flashlight
[OK: contains "banishing the darkness"]
